  <section id="problem" class="cs-section container">
    <div class="cs-kicker">01 &mdash; PROBLEM</div>
    <h2 class="cs-h2">Checkout mixed order completion with everything else</h2>
    <p class="cs-lead">By the time users reach checkout, they are no longer exploring &mdash; they are trying to confirm the rental, resolve required logistics, pay, and know what happens next. The old checkout mixed that with <strong style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--text)">account creation, optional prompts, and editing paths</strong>, creating extra opportunities to pause, hit errors, or leave after users had already shown purchase intent.</p>

    <h3 class="cs-h3" style="margin-top: clamp(36px, 6vw, 52px)">Quantitative signals</h3>
    <div class="cs-two-col" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); margin-top: 20px">
      <div>
        <div class="cs-media" style="aspect-ratio: 4 / 3">
          <img class="modal-target" src="ga4_cross_platform.png" alt="GA4 cross-platform funnel comparison" data-modal-gallery="ga4-checkout">
        </div>
        <div class="cs-label" style="margin-top: 8px">Cross-platform comparison</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="cs-media" style="aspect-ratio: 4 / 3">
          <img class="modal-target" src="ga4_detailed_breakdown.png" alt="GA4 detailed UX breakdown" data-modal-gallery="ga4-checkout">
        </div>
        <div class="cs-label" style="margin-top: 8px">Detailed UX breakdown</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="cs-media" style="aspect-ratio: 4 / 3">
          <img class="modal-target" src="ga4_mobile_app.png" alt="GA4 mobile app completion" data-modal-gallery="ga4-checkout">
        </div>
        <div class="cs-label" style="margin-top: 8px">Mobile app completion</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cs-breakdown-grid">
      <div class="cs-breakdown-card">
        <div class="cs-subhead">Mobile drops ~2&times; more than desktop</div>
        <p class="cs-text">From begin_checkout &rarr; purchase, web completed at ~84%; mobile web at ~46%.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-breakdown-card">
        <div class="cs-subhead">The largest drop happens before checkout begins</div>
        <p class="cs-text">From add_to_cart &rarr; begin_checkout, ~49% continued on web, ~34% on mobile web &mdash; over 60% of mobile users abandoned after adding items.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-breakdown-card">
        <div class="cs-subhead">Once users entered checkout, later-stage completion was high</div>
        <p class="cs-text">Among tracked web and mobile-web sessions, completion across payment and purchase steps was ~97&ndash;99% &mdash; friction was concentrated around entry, account state, and early commitment moments.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-breakdown-card">
        <div class="cs-subhead">Mobile app tracking is unreliable</div>
        <p class="cs-text">Purchase events exceeded checkout-initiation events in the app, indicating missing funnel instrumentation &mdash; one reason the app was excluded from scope.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cs-pullquote">
      <p>Checkout was not the largest funnel leak &mdash; but it was a <span class="accent">high-value moment</span> where avoidable friction could lose users who were already ready to book.</p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="cs-h3" style="margin-top: clamp(36px, 6vw, 52px)">Qualitative signals</h3>
    <p class="cs-lead" style="margin-top: 12px">Session recordings and walkthroughs of the legacy flow surfaced four recurring patterns.</p>

    <div class="cs-breakdown-grid">
      <div class="cs-breakdown-card">
        <div class="cs-subhead">A &middot; Decision loops</div>
        <div class="cs-media" style="aspect-ratio: 4 / 3">
          <img class="modal-target" src="qual1.png" alt="Links pulling users out of checkout" data-modal-gallery="checkout-qual">
        </div>
        <p class="cs-text" style="margin-top: 12px">Links back to cart, trip, and supporting pages pulled users out of checkout and back into decision mode.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-breakdown-card">
        <div class="cs-subhead">B &middot; Mobile review friction</div>
        <div class="cs-media" style="aspect-ratio: 4 / 3">
          <img class="modal-target" src="qual2.png" alt="Long scroll and persistent UI on mobile" data-modal-gallery="checkout-qual">
        </div>
        <p class="cs-text" style="margin-top: 12px">Long scroll, persistent UI, and a heavy footer made reviewing the order harder on mobile.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-breakdown-card">
        <div class="cs-subhead">C &middot; Flow interruptions</div>
        <div class="cs-media" style="aspect-ratio: 4 / 3">
          <img class="modal-target" src="qual3.png" alt="Login, payment, and password errors" data-modal-gallery="checkout-qual">
        </div>
        <p class="cs-text" style="margin-top: 12px">Login, payment, password, and iframe errors interrupted the flow and broke confidence at the worst moment.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-breakdown-card">
        <div class="cs-subhead">D &middot; Completion uncertainty</div>
