    <h3 class="cs-h3" style="margin-top: clamp(44px, 7vw, 64px)">Design strategy: separate required checkout tasks from everything else</h3>
    <p class="cs-text" style="max-width: 68ch; margin-top: 14px">Each job got its own place in the flow, driven by what users were actually asking at the commitment moment.</p>

    <div class="cs-breakdown-grid">
      <div class="cs-breakdown-card">
        <div class="cs-subhead">IDENTITY</div>
        <p class="cs-text" style="font-style: italic">&ldquo;Don't make me lose my progress if account creation fails at the end.&rdquo;</p>
        <p class="cs-text" style="font-style: italic">&ldquo;Don't make account state confusing.&rdquo;</p>
        <p class="cs-breakdown-principle"><strong>&rarr; Resolve identity earlier.</strong> OTP verification; remove the guest/password split.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-breakdown-card">
        <div class="cs-subhead">COMPLETION</div>
        <p class="cs-text" style="font-style: italic">&ldquo;Let me understand the whole task before I commit.&rdquo;</p>
        <p class="cs-text" style="font-style: italic">&ldquo;Tell me what's wrong in context.&rdquo;</p>
        <p class="cs-text" style="font-style: italic">&ldquo;Show progress while keeping review possible.&rdquo;</p>
        <p class="cs-breakdown-principle"><strong>&rarr; Keep required rental tasks in checkout.</strong> One-page checkout, section validation, collapsed completed sections.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-breakdown-card">
        <div class="cs-subhead">FOCUS</div>
        <p class="cs-text" style="font-style: italic">&ldquo;Don't ask nonessential questions before I finish.&rdquo;</p>
        <p class="cs-text" style="font-style: italic">&ldquo;Don't interrupt purchase with a secondary goal.&rdquo;</p>
        <p class="cs-text" style="font-style: italic">&ldquo;Don't pull me back into decision mode.&rdquo;</p>
        <p class="cs-breakdown-principle"><strong>&rarr; Move optional tasks after purchase.</strong> Survey and app prompts moved to confirmation; trip and cart editing minimized during checkout.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
